  "text": "with energy density and pressure [CITATION_1] such that \u0393\u03c6 2 represents the rate of energy flow out of the field \u03c6. Higher power dependence on\u03c6 will not change our argument. A reasonably loose constraint on the rate of energy production is that it is smaller that the production of the full present energy in one Hubble time.",
